{{Quote|Wait until we're in the ''Falcon'', a few light years away from here.|[[Han Solo]], to [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]]|<ref name="Skywalker Strikes">[[Star Wars (2015) 1|''Star Wars'' (2015) 1]]</ref>}}
The '''light-year'''<ref name="Trkn">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> (also spelled "light year")<ref name="Skywalker Strikes" /> was a unit of distance used in astronomy.<ref name="Trkn" /> It corresponded to the distance that light traveled in a [[standard year]], which was approximately 9.5 trillion [[kilometer]]s.<ref name="Falcon 61">{{BuildFalconCite|61|Guide to the Galaxy}}</ref>
